functions.description:
Initialize the client with user-provided API key and secret.
This should run when the user enters their API key/secret.
Returns the user's email address.
functions.name: INITIALIZECLIENT

functions.description: Returns the bid/ask prices of the given market.
functions.name: MARKETBBO

parameters.description: Market symbol, e.g. "ES 20250620 CME Future"
parameters.name: symbol

parameters.description: Market venue, e.g. "CME"
parameters.name: venue

functions.description:
Stream the bid/ask/last prices of a market in real-time. Or other fields if specified.

For the field params, the possible values are: askPrice, askSize, bidPrice, bidSize, lastPrice, lastSize, lastSettlementPrice, timestamp, dividend, dividendYield, epsAdj, high24h, low24h, marketCap, open24h, openInterest, priceToEarnings, sessionHigh, sessionLow, sessionOpen, sessionVolume, sharesOutstandingWeightedAdj, symbol, timestamp, volume24h, volume30d
functions.name: STREAMMARKETTICKER

parameters.description: Market symbol, e.g. "ES 20250620 CME Future"
parameters.name: symbol

parameters.description: Market venue, e.g. "CME"
parameters.name: venue

parameters.description: List of fields to stream, default value is ["bidPrice","askPrice","lastPrice"]
parameters.name: fields

functions.description: Returns the mid price of a the given market.
functions.name: MARKETMID

parameters.description: Market symbol, e.g. "ES 20250620 CME Future"
parameters.name: symbol

parameters.description: Market venue, e.g. "CME"
parameters.name: venue

functions.description:
Get the bid/ask/last price and size of a market.
Returns: bid price, bid size, ask price, ask size, last price, last size.
For the field params, the possible values are: askPrice, askSize, bidPrice, bidSize, lastPrice, lastSize, lastSettlementPrice, timestamp, dividend, dividendYield, epsAdj, high24h, low24h, marketCap, open24h, openInterest, priceToEarnings, sessionHigh, sessionLow, sessionOpen, sessionVolume, sharesOutstandingWeightedAdj, symbol, timestamp, volume24h, volume30d
functions.name: MARKETTICKER

parameters.description: Market symbol, e.g. "ES 20250620 CME Future"
parameters.name: symbol

parameters.description: Market venue, e.g. "CME"
parameters.name: venue

parameters.description: List of fields to stream, default value is ["bidPrice","bidSize","askPrice","askSize","lastPrice","lastSize"]
parameters.name: fields

functions.description: Returns a list accounts for a given API key/secret.
functions.name: ACCOUNTLIST

functions.description:
Stream the positions for a given account in real-time, ensuring the same structure as accountPositions.
Any symbols not in the account will be returned with zero values.
functions.name: STREAMACCOUNTPOSITIONVALUES

parameters.description: Account name, gotten from accountList function.
parameters.name: account_name

parameters.description: List of market symbols for the positions, e.g. ["ES 20250620 CME Future", "NQ 20250620 CME Future"].
parameters.name: symbols

parameters.description: If true, show all positions in the account.
parameters.name: show_all

functions.description: Returns account Pnl information: cash excess, equity, position margin, purchasing power, realized pnl, unrealized pnl, total margin, yesterday equity
functions.name: ACCOUNTPNL

parameters.description: Account name, gotten from accountList function.
parameters.name: account_name

parameters.description: Account name, gotten from accountList function.
parameters.name: account_name

functions.description: Get the list of symbols available for a given market.
functions.name: DERIVEFUTURESSYMBOL

parameters.description: Base name, e.g. "ES", "NQ", "RTY"
parameters.name: base_name

parameters.description: Expiration date, accepts several formats. e.g. "20250620", or "M5"/"M25" for June 2025, "Jun25"
parameters.name: expiration

parameters.description: Market name, e.g. "ES", "NQ", "RTY"
parameters.name: market_name

functions.description: Gets fills analysis for a given account and string of symbols for the current trading day.
functions.name: STREAMFILLSANALYSIS

parameters.description: Account name, gotten from accountList function.
parameters.name: accountName

parameters.description: Market symbols, e.g. ["ES 20250620 CME Future", "NQ 20250620 CME Future"]
parameters.name: symbols

parameters.description: Number of days to look back, default is 1 day.
parameters.name: number_of_days
